01:46.978 --> 01:49.211
Oh, uh, these are
taken. Sorry. Big family.

01:50.397 --> 01:51.422
Vultures.

01:51.433 --> 01:53.011
Get here early if you want a good spot.

01:53.022 --> 01:55.371
Mariana, chill. I mean, maybe
we should let people sit here

01:55.382 --> 01:57.670
- if they're not gonna...
- No, they're gonna be here.

02:00.132 --> 02:01.572
LENA: Is she answering?

02:02.201 --> 02:03.659
STEF: Hey, Callie, it's me. Again.

02:03.669 --> 02:05.349
Please, uh, call me
back when you get this.

02:05.938 --> 02:07.630
I don't know how long
we can wait for them.

02:07.640 --> 02:09.006
I will try again.

02:10.134 --> 02:11.168
- Hey.
- Hey, Robert.

02:11.179 --> 02:12.917
- Nice to see you.
- So good of you to come.

02:12.928 --> 02:15.269
Listen, I got a little gift
here for Callie. Where is she?

02:15.279 --> 02:16.813
Uh, have you guys seen Brandon?

02:18.182 --> 02:21.317
Oh, they, uh... They
might not be coming.

02:22.353 --> 02:23.586
What? Why?

02:25.957 --> 02:28.224
Well, it's, uh... It's
been a crazy few days.

02:35.132 --> 02:37.591
MARIANA: Jesus, get up.

02:37.601 --> 02:39.259
Go away.

02:39.269 --> 02:40.928
Believe me, I would love to.

02:40.938 --> 02:42.262
It smells like socks in here.

02:42.272 --> 02:44.482
But I need your help cleaning
out the backyard for Moms.

02:44.493 --> 02:46.994
Go find someone who
didn't fail junior year.

02:47.710 --> 02:48.735
(SIGHS)

02:48.745 --> 02:50.838
Look, I know you're bummed,

02:51.213 --> 02:54.106
but Moms told us that we need to
get this done today, so get up.

02:54.116 --> 02:55.474
You're so annoying.

02:55.484 --> 02:58.144
Well, then you're gonna love not being
in the same class as me.

02:58.154 --> 03:00.013
- Oh, that's mean.
- (MARIANA CHUCKLES)

03:00.023 --> 03:02.314
Look, you worked your ass off.

03:02.324 --> 03:04.183
You should be proud of yourself.

03:04.193 --> 03:05.283
I am.

03:05.293 --> 03:07.886
Okay, but you're my sister, Mariana.

03:07.896 --> 03:10.321
What about Emma?
You know how she feels about school.

03:10.331 --> 03:13.158
You really think she's
gonna want to date a junior?

03:13.168 --> 03:14.259
She loves you.

03:14.269 --> 03:15.869
Now come on.

03:20.809 --> 03:23.709
Seriously, Mariana, what
is the freaking rush?

03:27.048 --> 03:28.447
Whoa, what's going on?

03:29.817 --> 03:32.851
Well, your senior project
is worth four credits.

03:34.188 --> 03:36.352
Which is how much room
you need in your schedule

03:36.363 --> 03:37.548
to retake math next year

03:37.558 --> 03:39.583
So we're building a treehouse, babe.

03:39.593 --> 03:41.059
So you get to be a senior.

03:44.744 --> 03:47.723
Get that tool belt on, baby. Let's go!

03:47.734 --> 03:49.300
(STAMMERING) Okay.

03:50.904 --> 03:52.336
(DOORBELL RINGS)

03:56.308 --> 03:58.541
- Can I help you?
- Can we have a word?

04:02.514 --> 04:04.974
This is my supervisor, Agent Jordan.

04:04.984 --> 04:07.751
You make a habit of interfering
with federal government business?

04:09.454 --> 04:12.347
- I didn't...
- ICE is essential to national security.

04:12.357 --> 04:15.016
If you subpoena Agent
Allen, you risk exposing

04:15.026 --> 04:16.851
the way we work to the bad guys.

04:16.861 --> 04:18.385
Is that what you want?

04:18.394 --> 04:21.857
If "the way you work"
is unethical, then yes.

04:21.868 --> 04:24.458
You think it's ethical to help
your friend escape custody?

04:24.468 --> 04:25.701
Hide out in a church?

04:27.805 --> 04:29.571
You're in over your head, Miss Foster.

04:42.619 --> 04:44.978
Thank you so much for doing this.

04:44.988 --> 04:47.655
Yeah, well, you try
saying no to your sister.

04:49.759 --> 04:50.991
Hey, uhm...

04:52.261 --> 04:54.053
I hope you know how sorry I am

04:54.063 --> 04:55.796
for leaving like I did.

04:57.199 --> 04:58.565
I thought I was in the way,

05:00.169 --> 05:02.762
and I'm just not that great

05:02.772 --> 05:04.328
at tough conversations.

05:04.338 --> 05:05.864
I get it.

05:05.874 --> 05:08.299
Okay, you're just doing
the best you can, right?

05:08.309 --> 05:09.768
Yeah.

05:09.778 --> 05:10.902
It's cool.

05:10.912 --> 05:13.279
Okay? We've got the most
awesome family in the world,

05:14.515 --> 05:16.474
so we're good.

05:16.484 --> 05:17.650
Really.

05:19.688 --> 05:21.086
Where's B?

05:22.289 --> 05:24.581
Uh, he's driving up to Marin county.

05:24.591 --> 05:26.016
He's been there every weekend.

05:26.026 --> 05:28.118
I thought with graduation
coming up, he'd be home.

05:28.128 --> 05:30.487
He was, but Grace took a turn.

05:30.497 --> 05:33.356
So he left this morning.
He wanted to be with her.

05:33.366 --> 05:34.758
Shit.

05:34.768 --> 05:36.259
Is he still her, uh,

05:36.269 --> 05:37.827
what do you call it, proxy?

05:37.837 --> 05:39.132
Yeah, he and I talked about it.

05:39.143 --> 05:41.588
It's just, you know, something
that he wants to do for her.

05:41.599 --> 05:44.433
I don't know how he's supposed to
make a decision like that at his age?

05:44.443 --> 05:46.769
I know. And trust me,
her mom is none too happy

05:46.779 --> 05:48.045
about it, either.

05:59.657 --> 06:01.224
SUSAN: Grace. Sweetie.

06:02.427 --> 06:03.459
Look who's here.

06:04.596 --> 06:05.596
Look.

06:08.600 --> 06:09.632
You're back.

06:11.103 --> 06:12.703
I'll give you guys
some time to catch up.

06:15.206 --> 06:16.238
Okay.

06:25.950 --> 06:27.116
How you feeling?

06:29.185 --> 06:31.518
Like a million bucks. (CHUCKLES)

06:38.928 --> 06:40.294
What day is it?

06:42.431 --> 06:43.564
Friday.

06:45.368 --> 06:46.499
But when's graduation?

06:47.669 --> 06:48.802
Sunday.

06:52.340 --> 06:53.807
- What are you...
- I just...

06:57.312 --> 06:58.611
just missed you.

07:08.045 --> 07:09.847
NOAH: So, you coming to
help out at the church

07:09.858 --> 07:11.652
with the rummage sale tomorrow?

07:12.225 --> 07:13.316
Oh, no.

07:13.326 --> 07:16.719
Sorry. Um, Taylor,
Declan, and I have this,

07:16.729 --> 07:18.421
like, meet-and-greet at Game Realm.

07:18.431 --> 07:20.690
We're basically just gonna, you know,

07:20.700 --> 07:23.525
sell Eminent Power
merch and talk with fans

07:23.535 --> 07:24.827
and take pictures and stuff.

07:24.837 --> 07:26.670
Okay, Mr. Superstar.

07:28.307 --> 07:31.033
I'm sorry. It's my job.

07:31.043 --> 07:32.242
Got it.

07:35.114 --> 07:37.006
Oh, damn. I'm so sorry.

07:37.016 --> 07:38.774
Dude, this was an expensive shirt.

07:38.784 --> 07:42.143
Okay, but then why did you
wear it to build the treehouse?

07:42.153 --> 07:43.552
You afraid Declan might stop by?

07:44.622 --> 07:45.847
What does that mean?

07:45.857 --> 07:48.917
Okay. It's just with
the hair and the clothes

07:48.927 --> 07:50.819
and your attitude.

07:50.829 --> 07:53.196
I mean, it's just kinda
like where did Jude go?

07:53.898 --> 07:55.790
I thought you got into
all this streaming stuff

07:55.800 --> 07:57.891
so you could be a role
model to other gaymers.

07:57.901 --> 08:01.428
But now it's all about the money
and the clothes and your fans.

08:01.438 --> 08:03.504
Don't act like you care
about them when you don't.

08:04.875 --> 08:06.575
You just care that you have them.

08:07.444 --> 08:09.102
Wow!

08:09.112 --> 08:11.779
Well, if that's how you feel, then
why don't you break up with me?

08:12.982 --> 08:15.142
I think that's the best idea
you've had in a long time.

08:21.757 --> 08:22.857
What is it?

08:23.960 --> 08:25.492
It's a stay of removal.

08:27.029 --> 08:28.687
What? Is it...

08:28.697 --> 08:32.823
You get to stay in the country
as long as you don't commit any crimes.

08:32.833 --> 08:36.402
- (CRYING)
- XIMENA: Oh, my God.

08:38.506 --> 08:39.831
How did this happen?

08:39.841 --> 08:41.799
Well, ICE didn't want the bad publicity

08:41.808 --> 08:43.902
of Allen having to testify.

08:43.912 --> 08:46.537
I mean, it's not a path
to citizenship, but...

08:46.547 --> 08:49.447
But for now, it keeps us together.

08:51.752 --> 08:53.844
But what about Ximena's DACA?

08:53.854 --> 08:55.512
Could this effect that?

08:55.522 --> 08:58.482
No. ICE can't make a
decision on her DACA,

08:58.492 --> 09:02.552
but they definitely can issue
a recommendation to deny it.

09:02.562 --> 09:05.321
Would they do that?

09:05.331 --> 09:07.734
If they're mad that we tried
to subpoena one of their agents.

09:07.745 --> 09:10.913
If they do, we'll go public
with everything we know.

09:11.938 --> 09:13.304
We're not gonna let that happen.

09:17.243 --> 09:18.801
What if we both get the internship?

09:18.811 --> 09:21.144
Oh, my God, how sick would that be?

09:27.085 --> 09:28.151
You invited Wyatt?

09:29.487 --> 09:31.980
I mean, he used to
work construction, so...

09:31.990 --> 09:33.782
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

09:33.792 --> 09:35.491
EMMA: Okay, but Logan's here too.

09:36.494 --> 09:38.085
Well, what was I supposed to do?

09:38.095 --> 09:39.395
I mean, he lives next door.

09:40.898 --> 09:44.225
So have you decided
who gets the final rose?

09:44.235 --> 09:45.634
No.

09:47.905 --> 09:50.264
But I think I need to cut Wyatt loose.

09:50.274 --> 09:53.567
It's just he's graduating,
and he wants to, like,

09:53.577 --> 09:55.335
wander the world or whatever.

09:55.345 --> 09:57.370
And we all know long
distance doesn't work.

09:57.380 --> 09:59.306
(CHUCKLES) No kidding.

09:59.316 --> 10:01.074
It's bad enough that I might have to go

10:01.084 --> 10:03.276
to L.A. for the summer,
but what about after that?

10:03.286 --> 10:05.486
If I end up at MIT

10:06.522 --> 10:07.721
and Jesus stays here,

10:09.326 --> 10:10.758
San Diego to Boston,

10:12.394 --> 10:14.161
that's a way long distance, you know?

10:17.266 --> 10:19.258
You're not thinking about, like...

10:19.268 --> 10:20.633
No. God, no.

10:22.604 --> 10:23.670
It's just hard.

10:24.806 --> 10:26.573
Okay. Well, good.

10:29.810 --> 10:32.736
You know, I should at least
thank Wyatt for coming, right?

10:32.746 --> 10:34.280
Mm-hmm.

10:35.850 --> 10:37.308
How do I look? Cute?

10:37.318 --> 10:38.584
Mm-hmm.

10:39.954 --> 10:41.320
(CELL PHONE CHIMING)

10:50.230 --> 10:51.230
What?

10:53.233 --> 10:55.758
Isn't there another
way you can get Molloy?

10:55.768 --> 10:57.560
Not without taking Gray down.

10:57.570 --> 10:59.596
And if I do that, he goes right to IA...

10:59.606 --> 11:00.830
(SIGHS)

11:00.840 --> 11:02.499
... and lets them know that I lied

11:02.509 --> 11:04.309
during the investigation
into Mike's shooting.

11:05.544 --> 11:07.036
Well, I mean,

11:07.046 --> 11:09.472
this has been weighing on
you for such a long time.

11:09.482 --> 11:12.949
I can't afford to lose my
job or my pension, can I?

11:16.855 --> 11:19.789
You know, Callie, you really are
gonna make a great lawyer one day.

11:22.127 --> 11:24.852
You asked me why I can't wait a year

11:24.862 --> 11:26.695
to apply to the five-year law program.

11:28.166 --> 11:30.900
What just happened, that's why.

11:32.170 --> 11:35.997
Like, there are so many
broken, corrupt systems

11:36.007 --> 11:39.366
in this country, and, I
mean, it's only getting worse.

11:39.376 --> 11:42.102
We both know the Sinfuegos got lucky.

11:42.112 --> 11:43.970
Very lucky.

11:43.980 --> 11:46.040
But most people in their situation

11:46.050 --> 11:48.675
don't have access to the
same resources that they did.

11:48.685 --> 11:50.010
You mean you?

11:50.020 --> 11:52.109
Listen, Callie, you've done
so much for them already.

11:52.120 --> 11:55.423
No. No, I meant you and
all the law students.

11:57.527 --> 12:01.587
But the people I wanna help
don't have time on their side.

12:01.597 --> 12:05.758
Like, think about how many families
could be torn apart in a year.

12:05.768 --> 12:08.694
How many kids could
have their lives ruined

12:08.704 --> 12:12.897
because of a legal system that is
completely stacked against them.

12:12.907 --> 12:14.899
Callie...

12:14.909 --> 12:16.809
you really are a force
of nature, you know that?

12:17.992 --> 12:19.438
This world's gonna be a better place

12:19.448 --> 12:21.051
with you out there
fighting for what's right.

12:21.062 --> 12:22.328
There's no doubt about that.

12:23.552 --> 12:27.053
And we would be very lucky to
have you in our law program.

12:28.422 --> 12:29.821
Now that being said,

12:30.857 --> 12:32.558
it's probably not
gonna happen this year.

12:51.014 --> 12:52.432
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

12:53.557 --> 12:55.649
Gray, you got a sec?

12:55.659 --> 12:57.651
I'm really not in the
mood for another lecture

12:57.661 --> 12:59.220
on the moral high-ground, Foster.

12:59.230 --> 13:00.895
Well, I would like to, uh...

13:03.234 --> 13:04.866
I'd like to call a truce, please.

13:06.469 --> 13:08.961
I think that this has gone
on, uh, a little too long.

13:08.971 --> 13:10.296
I almost did something stupid.

13:10.306 --> 13:12.632
I almost put Patrick Molloy's
name on a warrant list

13:12.642 --> 13:14.133
without a judge's order.

13:14.143 --> 13:16.223
- That would have been stupid.
- I'm more than aware.

13:17.547 --> 13:19.046
I cannot afford to lose my job.

13:20.783 --> 13:22.774
So I, uh...

13:22.784 --> 13:25.110
just wanna let this
whole Molloy thing go.

13:25.120 --> 13:26.211
Wise decision.

13:26.221 --> 13:27.812
Thank you.

13:27.822 --> 13:30.257
I do need one thing from you, however.

13:32.026 --> 13:34.219
I need to know that you
will not go to IA on me,

13:34.229 --> 13:37.631
and I need to know that you will
leave Kyle Snow alone, please.

13:38.933 --> 13:40.699
You don't narc on me,
I don't narc on you.

13:45.072 --> 13:46.664
I guess we're good.

13:46.674 --> 13:50.401
But honestly, Gray,
it doesn't bother you that you left

13:50.411 --> 13:52.236
a child molester on the street?

13:52.246 --> 13:53.771
Really?

13:53.781 --> 13:56.994
It would have bothered me a lot more
to leave a murderer on the street.

13:57.784 --> 13:59.049
You have to pick your battles.

14:01.621 --> 14:03.020
Fair enough.

14:04.957 --> 14:06.791
You can't win 'em all, right?

14:20.439 --> 14:22.063
You think that was enough?

14:22.073 --> 14:24.667
With your testimony? Absolutely.

14:24.677 --> 14:26.101
Hey...

14:26.111 --> 14:28.244
You sure you wanna go to IA with this?

14:34.051 --> 14:35.677
Thank you so much for watching.

14:35.687 --> 14:37.679
And then he said I'm,
like, turning into you,

14:37.689 --> 14:40.381
and I'm like whatever.

14:40.391 --> 14:41.949
I'm never supposed to change?

14:41.959 --> 14:43.250
That is total BS.

14:43.261 --> 14:46.477
He's jealous of all the success
you're having. Trust me, it happens.

14:48.118 --> 14:49.150
Hi.

14:50.534 --> 14:51.958
Sorry, I'm a little...

14:51.968 --> 14:54.361
Uh, how did you...

14:54.371 --> 14:56.996
How did you conquer
the crystal mountain?

14:57.006 --> 14:58.898
(CHUCKLES) Oh, um...

14:58.908 --> 15:01.968
you have to hit the guard
trolls with an onyx bomb.

15:01.978 --> 15:04.403
They're vulnerable to minerals.

15:04.413 --> 15:05.871
Of course.

15:05.881 --> 15:07.340
I should have thought of that.

15:07.350 --> 15:08.384
I'm so dumb.

15:08.395 --> 15:10.066
Hey, bud, we got a
lot of people waiting.

15:10.077 --> 15:11.544
Gotta keep things moving, you know?

15:11.554 --> 15:13.579
Right. Sorry.

15:13.589 --> 15:15.648
- So nice to meet you.
- Okay, let's go.

15:15.658 --> 15:17.082
Dude, don't be rude.

15:17.092 --> 15:18.250
Who gives a crap.

15:18.260 --> 15:19.819
The only bummer about these things

15:19.829 --> 15:21.828
is realizing how many
losers watch our streams.

15:32.674 --> 15:33.998
- Hey.
- Hey!

15:34.008 --> 15:35.467
- How are you?
- (BOTH KISSING)

15:35.477 --> 15:36.724
Thank you so much for coming.

15:36.735 --> 15:38.733
Soon as we finish this
up, you won't have to worry

15:38.744 --> 15:40.671
about dating a lowly junior.

15:40.681 --> 15:42.072
- I never...
- Emma!

15:42.082 --> 15:44.384
Oh, my God, I just got an
email from the Bandt Foundation.

15:44.395 --> 15:45.609
Oh, my God. What did they say?

15:45.619 --> 15:47.919
I don't know. I haven't
seen it. Check your phone.

15:51.057 --> 15:53.684
Okay. Deep breath.

15:53.694 --> 15:56.318
Chances are neither one of
us got it. So let's just...

15:56.328 --> 15:59.054
rip off the Band-Aid
and see what they said.

15:59.064 --> 16:00.723
One,

16:00.733 --> 16:02.091
two,

16:02.101 --> 16:03.233
three.

16:07.273 --> 16:09.064
You were right.

16:09.074 --> 16:10.274
I didn't get in.

16:11.911 --> 16:14.068
(GIGGLING)

16:14.078 --> 16:15.445
- Congrats.
- Congrats.

16:16.815 --> 16:18.014
EMMA: I'm sorry.

16:21.620 --> 16:25.855
(PLAYING SLOW MELODY)

16:31.929 --> 16:33.962
I want you to promise me something.

16:35.299 --> 16:37.566
I want you to go to Coachella even if...

16:39.036 --> 16:40.536
even if I can't.

16:47.477 --> 16:48.576
Okay.

16:50.880 --> 16:52.146
I promise.

16:53.249 --> 16:55.909
Unless the headliner sucks.

16:55.919 --> 16:57.510
Then you can sell the tickets online.

16:57.520 --> 16:58.920
(CHUCKLES)

17:02.224 --> 17:03.723
We should have played there.

17:06.060 --> 17:07.894
We would have rocked that place.

17:10.065 --> 17:14.067
I'm sorry that we never
really got a chance to gig out.

17:19.374 --> 17:21.073
We'll always have the bagel shop.

17:27.146 --> 17:29.548
(SIGHS) I made my mom my proxy.

17:33.153 --> 17:34.286
You did?

17:35.289 --> 17:38.214
Yeah, we had a long talk and, uh,

17:38.224 --> 17:39.457
and she...

17:41.695 --> 17:42.794
She got it.

17:45.164 --> 17:47.144
- A... are you sure, 'cause I...
- I'm sure.

17:47.834 --> 17:49.367
It's the right thing to do.

17:51.137 --> 17:52.971
For her and...

17:55.574 --> 17:56.773
you.

18:06.485 --> 18:08.184
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

18:09.722 --> 18:11.679
All right, well, that's good to hear.

18:11.689 --> 18:12.989
Thanks for getting back to me.

18:15.593 --> 18:17.351
So they picked up Molloy, and he talked.

18:17.361 --> 18:18.594
So Gray is going down, too.

18:19.697 --> 18:21.188
That is incredible.

18:21.198 --> 18:22.891
Any word from IA?

18:22.901 --> 18:24.893
No, but, um,

18:24.903 --> 18:26.828
it felt good to come clean.

18:26.838 --> 18:28.237
About everything, you know.

18:29.472 --> 18:31.231
Maybe it's time for a career change.

18:31.241 --> 18:32.633
Do a little something different.

18:32.643 --> 18:35.143
Really kinda scary to say that but...

18:36.312 --> 18:38.204
Thank you so much for understanding.

18:38.214 --> 18:39.514
This was something I had to do.

18:40.431 --> 18:42.409
Honey, the only thing
that matters is that you do

18:42.419 --> 18:44.310
what makes you feel good about yourself.

18:44.320 --> 18:46.319
Everything else works
itself out in the end.

18:47.489 --> 18:48.589
We'll be fine.

18:51.027 --> 18:52.459
- I love you.
- I love you.

18:54.229 --> 18:56.564
Okay, get to work. Slacker.

19:00.870 --> 19:02.169
(GRUNTS)

19:05.239 --> 19:06.272
Hi.

19:09.277 --> 19:10.476
Yeah.

19:13.481 --> 19:14.681
You okay?

19:15.850 --> 19:18.076
I mean, my life's pretty much ruined,

19:18.086 --> 19:19.677
but I'm fine.

19:19.687 --> 19:22.854
Mariana, who cares if you
didn't get some dumb internship?

19:24.058 --> 19:26.584
You're the most
single-minded person I know.

19:26.594 --> 19:28.552
When you want something, you get it.

19:28.562 --> 19:30.621
I mean, look at this,
what you did for me.

19:30.631 --> 19:32.764
I get to be a senior because of you.

19:33.901 --> 19:35.993
Yeah, but, I mean, you
did all the hard work.

19:36.003 --> 19:38.227
Yeah, maybe, but...

19:38.237 --> 19:39.770
you figured out how to make it happen.

19:41.874 --> 19:43.800
You're gonna be fine.

19:43.810 --> 19:45.076
I know it.

19:49.082 --> 19:50.214
Remember when we were kids,

19:51.350 --> 19:52.850
we always wanted a magic treehouse.

19:54.486 --> 19:56.078
Now we got one.

19:56.088 --> 19:58.421
And it's gonna take you
anywhere you wanna go.

20:19.376 --> 20:20.776
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

20:24.715 --> 20:28.942
(VOICE BREAKING) ♪ Look at this life ♪

20:28.952 --> 20:31.152
♪ I'm starting with you ♪

20:35.558 --> 20:40.053
♪ The brightest of lights ♪

20:40.063 --> 20:43.931
♪ Shining on the beautiful view ♪

20:45.134 --> 20:49.461
♪ Deep in your eyes ♪

20:49.471 --> 20:54.775
♪ I found a love that's
wonderful and true ♪

20:56.611 --> 20:59.212
♪ All the things I'm gonna do ♪

21:00.849 --> 21:02.948
(CRYING)

21:04.852 --> 21:07.987
♪ All the things I'm gonna do ♪

21:10.124 --> 21:13.625
♪ Gonna do with you ♪

21:25.552 --> 21:27.052
Jesus, we gotta go.

21:28.089 --> 21:30.581
LENA: All right, that's the last of it.

21:30.591 --> 21:31.881
(SIGHS)

21:31.891 --> 21:33.850
All right, Missy,

21:33.860 --> 21:36.152
now that we've got
you alone for a second.

21:36.162 --> 21:37.386
Yeah?

21:37.396 --> 21:40.857
We just want to make sure that
you take in tomorrow, okay?

21:40.867 --> 21:43.101
Take it all in.
Graduating is kind of a...

21:44.104 --> 21:45.128
It's kind of a big deal.

21:45.138 --> 21:46.662
LENA: Do you realize that, like,

21:46.672 --> 21:49.598
50 percent of kids who've
been in the foster system

21:49.608 --> 21:50.933
don't even graduate high school

21:50.943 --> 21:53.936
and then less than 10
percent go on to college?

21:53.946 --> 21:56.972
What you have accomplished is
nothing short of incredible, Cal.

21:56.982 --> 21:59.775
Okay? And we are so,
so very proud of you.

21:59.785 --> 22:01.343
(CHUCKLES)

22:01.353 --> 22:02.845
LENA: If someone would
have told me that day

22:02.855 --> 22:04.415
that I picked you up outside of juvie...

22:06.490 --> 22:08.590
that this is where you would end up...

22:11.195 --> 22:13.221
(BOTH LAUGHING)

22:13.231 --> 22:15.522
You're a fighter. You always have been.

22:15.532 --> 22:18.333
Now that you've started fighting for
yourself, look what's happened.

22:20.638 --> 22:21.703
Um...

22:23.006 --> 22:24.239
you told me...

22:25.608 --> 22:29.878
when I first got here, you
said I wasn't disposable.

22:32.983 --> 22:36.251
That meant so much, but...

22:37.553 --> 22:40.646
what means even more is how you've

22:40.656 --> 22:44.024
made me feel that way every day since.

22:48.164 --> 22:49.596
I love you, Moms.

22:51.600 --> 22:53.058
I love you, too.

22:53.068 --> 22:55.635
(ALL LAUGHING)

23:02.977 --> 23:05.636
In all the years I
spent in the audience,

23:05.646 --> 23:09.096
jealously listening to Sanchez
give these graduation speeches,

23:09.107 --> 23:11.289
it never occurred to me she
had to actually write them.

23:11.300 --> 23:12.343
This is painful.

23:12.353 --> 23:13.852
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

23:18.491 --> 23:19.757
Hey.

23:22.429 --> 23:23.695
B?

23:24.832 --> 23:26.198
She's gone.

23:27.367 --> 23:29.159
STEF: <i>Baby, I'm so sorry.</i>

23:29.169 --> 23:31.194
<i>I, uh, I can be up there in the morning.</i>

23:31.204 --> 23:32.804
<i>- I'll take a plane.</i>
- No, I wanna drive.

23:33.873 --> 23:37.141
I don't want to talk to anybody. I
just... I need to clear my head.

23:38.744 --> 23:40.369
<i>Are you sure, babe? Because I... </i>

23:40.379 --> 23:41.745
Yes, I'm fine, Mom.

23:44.217 --> 23:46.217
I'll be back in the morning
before you guys get up.

23:57.896 --> 24:01.156
So, uh, now the Sinfuegos
can stay in the country.

24:01.166 --> 24:03.325
Can you believe it? After all that?

24:03.335 --> 24:05.860
So now, we're just waiting
to hear about Ximena's DACA,

24:05.870 --> 24:08.270
and hopefully we should
know any day now, so...

24:12.442 --> 24:14.034
Um...

24:14.044 --> 24:16.544
So, uh, I know I told you

24:17.882 --> 24:20.741
I needed a little time to think about...

24:20.751 --> 24:25.011
Well, you know, to think about
you and Amanda and everything?

24:25.021 --> 24:27.580
- Uh-huh.
- And, um,

24:27.590 --> 24:30.416
it's been really confusing
because you're both

24:30.426 --> 24:32.593
these incredible people.

24:34.597 --> 24:38.556
But as much as I care about you,

24:38.566 --> 24:41.034
I, uh, I think I need to...

24:42.938 --> 24:44.237
see where things go with her.

24:49.477 --> 24:51.945
I can see why. She's pretty great.

24:54.216 --> 24:55.547
So are you, Callie.

25:00.854 --> 25:02.587
Don't forget that.

25:14.134 --> 25:15.366
(SOBBING QUIETLY)

25:31.450 --> 25:32.983
To hell with it.

25:52.971 --> 25:57.332
GRACE (SINGING):
<i>♪ I see those waves crashing ♪</i>

25:57.342 --> 26:01.535
<i>- ♪ But they can't touch us no ♪</i>
- (CROWD CHEERING)

26:01.545 --> 26:05.005
BOTH: ♪ Lightning on
the mountain flashing ♪

26:05.015 --> 26:08.408
♪ I say let it light our road ♪

26:08.418 --> 26:11.811
♪ Tell me what is time anyway ♪

26:11.821 --> 26:14.914
♪ I'll be by your side all the way ♪

26:14.924 --> 26:18.285
♪ We felt the time passing ♪

26:18.295 --> 26:20.953
♪ Flowing to a new start ♪

26:20.963 --> 26:24.357
♪ Dove in and there's no disguising ♪

26:24.367 --> 26:27.626
♪ Any other after mine ♪

26:27.636 --> 26:29.962
♪ What is time anyway? ♪

26:29.972 --> 26:32.264
♪ I'll be by your side ♪

26:32.274 --> 26:35.901
♪ All the way ♪

26:35.911 --> 26:38.436
BRANDON: <i>♪ I'll be by your side ♪</i>

26:38.446 --> 26:41.381
<i>♪ All the way ♪</i>

26:52.328 --> 26:55.021
Hey! Haven't seen you
do that in a while.

26:56.036 --> 26:57.135
Let me help.

27:00.474 --> 27:01.474
(SIGHS)

27:02.476 --> 27:04.042
Does this go with your new look?

27:05.145 --> 27:06.178
I don't really care.

27:07.747 --> 27:08.780
You okay, bud?

27:10.451 --> 27:13.843
Do you ever worry that
you sometimes might be

27:13.853 --> 27:15.578
kinda turning into a jerk?

27:15.588 --> 27:17.180
(CHUCKLES)

27:17.190 --> 27:19.182
Oh God, yes.

27:19.192 --> 27:23.260
I worry about that every
time I lose my temper at work,

27:24.430 --> 27:26.697
or I let Mom get the
better of me. Or you kids.

27:28.167 --> 27:30.125
And then I just remind myself that, um,

27:30.135 --> 27:33.328
I'm human and I'm
allowed to have feelings

27:33.338 --> 27:35.697
and get frustrated and make mistakes.

27:35.707 --> 27:38.008
Or bad decisions, even.

27:39.277 --> 27:43.146
And, uh, I'm only a jerk
if I don't make it better.

27:45.083 --> 27:46.907
I've been streaming

27:46.917 --> 27:49.284
with Taylor and Declan. At his place.

27:50.354 --> 27:51.420
I see.

27:52.589 --> 27:54.890
- Even after...
- Even after I said I wasn't.

27:56.560 --> 27:58.119
I'm sorry.

27:58.129 --> 27:59.129
Okay.

28:00.231 --> 28:01.671
And how are you gonna make it better?

28:29.458 --> 28:30.857
How did you find me?

28:32.194 --> 28:34.619
I checked your room to
see if you were back,

28:34.629 --> 28:37.355
and, um, I saw

28:37.365 --> 28:40.466
the Coachella tickets
Grace gave you on your desk.

28:48.609 --> 28:52.744
I can't imagine how
you're feeling right now,

28:55.449 --> 28:57.882
but do you really wanna miss graduation?

29:00.554 --> 29:02.879
I'm pretty sure Grace
would've wanted you to go.

29:02.889 --> 29:04.747
I don't...

29:04.757 --> 29:06.391
care about graduation.

29:09.229 --> 29:10.428
Okay, then.

29:15.101 --> 29:16.225
(CRYING): You should go.

29:16.235 --> 29:17.534
No, I'm not going anywhere.

29:24.910 --> 29:26.276
I can't believe she's gone.

29:30.515 --> 29:31.647
I know.

29:36.687 --> 29:38.279
(SOBS)

29:38.289 --> 29:39.622
It's not fair.

29:45.162 --> 29:46.620
I... I just...

29:46.630 --> 29:50.532
I hope that she knew
how much I loved her.

29:52.269 --> 29:53.568
Of course she did.

29:56.440 --> 29:57.839
What makes you so sure?

30:01.445 --> 30:03.844
Because I've been loved by you, Brandon.

30:05.881 --> 30:09.716
And it is a pretty powerful thing.

30:13.389 --> 30:14.421
Thank you for that.

30:18.494 --> 30:19.692
Grace knew.

30:22.030 --> 30:24.397
She knew that you loved her.

30:26.401 --> 30:29.735
And she knew how lucky she
was to have you in her life...

30:32.106 --> 30:33.498
even for a little while.

30:33.508 --> 30:36.008
(SOBBING)

30:43.784 --> 30:47.118
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

30:51.725 --> 30:55.051
(PEOPLE CHATTERING EXCITEDLY)

30:55.061 --> 30:56.194
(SIGHS)

30:57.330 --> 30:58.388
No sign of them?

30:58.398 --> 31:00.122
No.

31:00.132 --> 31:02.024
Damn!

31:02.034 --> 31:04.436
I can't believe that she would
miss this. She worked so hard.

31:04.447 --> 31:05.961
I know. Trust me.

31:05.971 --> 31:07.197
What did you get her?

31:07.207 --> 31:09.865
Oh, it's from Sophia.

31:09.875 --> 31:12.000
I probably shouldn't have
brought it to the ceremony.

31:12.010 --> 31:14.503
It's a raincoat. For
Portland. For school.

31:14.513 --> 31:15.837
Well, that was very thoughtful.

31:15.847 --> 31:18.014
She's gonna... She's
gonna need it for sure.

31:22.621 --> 31:24.187
Congratulations, Mr. Graduate.

31:25.857 --> 31:28.015
You finally excited about
going to Boston in the fall?

31:28.025 --> 31:29.049
I am.

31:29.059 --> 31:31.285
And thank you for your

31:31.295 --> 31:33.354
combo platter break-up speech/pep-talk.

31:33.364 --> 31:36.023
It really helped me
get my head on straight.

31:36.033 --> 31:37.666
Well, you're welcome.

31:38.869 --> 31:42.029
And hey, if you end up at
MIT like you always wanted,

31:42.039 --> 31:44.198
we'll both be in Boston,

31:44.208 --> 31:46.766
so maybe we can grab a
cup of coffee or something.

31:46.776 --> 31:50.144
I don't really think MIT
is gonna happen, but...

31:51.481 --> 31:54.107
if by some miracle it does,

31:54.117 --> 31:55.182
you're on.

31:59.222 --> 32:00.455
(KISSES)

32:07.929 --> 32:09.563
They'll be here, don't worry.

32:18.773 --> 32:20.197
You came?

32:20.207 --> 32:23.000
Well, I wasn't gonna bail
on Callie and Brandon.

32:23.010 --> 32:24.710
- (LAUGHS)
- What?

32:26.314 --> 32:28.640
You're a really good guy.

32:28.650 --> 32:29.948
I know!

32:32.320 --> 32:34.379
I quit Eminent Power.

32:34.389 --> 32:35.487
You did?

32:36.590 --> 32:40.659
Taylor and me are gonna go back to
being just Girl and One Gay Guy.

32:42.529 --> 32:44.454
And you were right.

32:44.464 --> 32:47.865
I kinda forgot why I
started doing all this.

32:49.869 --> 32:51.002
I'm sorry.

32:53.005 --> 32:54.005
You know,

32:55.140 --> 32:56.473
you're a really good guy, too.

33:02.748 --> 33:04.881
(CHATTERING)

33:12.390 --> 33:13.881
(GIGGLES)

33:13.891 --> 33:16.150
Did you just wave to Wyatt?

33:16.160 --> 33:18.586
Well, I didn't wanna break
up with him before graduation.

33:18.596 --> 33:21.623
Because you don't wanna
break up with him at all.

33:21.633 --> 33:23.032
(LAUGHING)

33:25.236 --> 33:27.135
That's gonna be us next year.

33:33.176 --> 33:35.135
- Any update?
- No. Unh-unh.

33:35.145 --> 33:37.371
Well, we gotta start soon.

33:37.381 --> 33:38.714
I know.

33:42.252 --> 33:43.551
LENA: Really soon.

33:51.428 --> 33:55.063
Welcome, students, parents, friends,

33:56.340 --> 33:59.074
and especially our
graduating senior class.

34:01.412 --> 34:03.813
We are so proud of each
and every one of you.

34:05.483 --> 34:08.116
What you've accomplished
over these past four years...

34:16.693 --> 34:18.451
You know what?

34:18.460 --> 34:20.654
I, uh, I did write a speech,

34:20.664 --> 34:23.755
and I worked really, really hard on it.

34:23.766 --> 34:26.099
But I've got two kids graduating today.

34:27.637 --> 34:29.460
And while very thoughtful,

34:29.471 --> 34:32.699
my speech doesn't really do justice
to everything I want to say to them

34:33.643 --> 34:35.067
and to the rest of my family,

34:35.077 --> 34:37.036
sitting out there in the audience

34:37.045 --> 34:42.007
and to each and every
one of you students who...

34:42.016 --> 34:44.909
You all feel like my
kids, one way or the other.

34:44.920 --> 34:46.978
- (AUDIENCE CHUCKLES)
- LENA: So, uh,

34:46.987 --> 34:49.722
I'm just gonna make it up as I go.

34:53.460 --> 34:54.694
These seniors,

34:55.996 --> 34:59.189
my first graduating class as principal,

34:59.199 --> 35:02.760
will always hold a
special place in my heart.

35:02.770 --> 35:04.662
And when I think about
everything we have gone

35:04.672 --> 35:06.664
through together,

35:06.674 --> 35:08.206
to arrive where we are today,

35:10.143 --> 35:11.977
it makes one thing really clear to me.

35:14.047 --> 35:16.338
There are so many roads to take

35:16.348 --> 35:18.015
to get to where you want to be in life.

35:19.251 --> 35:21.410
Life ain't easy. It's...

35:21.420 --> 35:22.853
It's gonna hit you hard.

35:24.523 --> 35:26.423
It's gonna put challenges in your path.

35:27.586 --> 35:30.045
It's gonna take you all kinds of places,

35:30.056 --> 35:31.519
sometimes giving you what you want,

35:31.529 --> 35:33.388
sometimes, what you need.

35:33.398 --> 35:35.423
Which might just be a kick in the ass.

35:35.433 --> 35:37.692
The trick is to enjoy the journey.

35:38.971 --> 35:41.671
And a big part of that
depends on who you travel with.

35:43.174 --> 35:45.274
I've made a lot of
mistakes in my life but...

35:46.945 --> 35:51.171
that's one thing I got
absolutely, positively,

35:51.181 --> 35:52.615
exactly right.

35:56.621 --> 35:58.553
(VOICE BREAKING): My family is my world.

36:00.324 --> 36:01.882
(LENA LAUGHING)

36:01.892 --> 36:05.051
And they have made this ride so joyful

36:05.061 --> 36:06.494
and so beautiful...

36:07.897 --> 36:12.299
so crazy and messy and...

36:14.370 --> 36:15.737
perfect.

36:19.009 --> 36:20.767
So thank you all.

36:20.777 --> 36:23.309
Thank you all so much for
taking this journey with us all.

36:25.380 --> 36:26.613
And remember...

36:27.683 --> 36:28.949
it's not where you come from,

36:30.019 --> 36:31.217
it's where you belong.

36:32.688 --> 36:34.988
And no matter where
this life takes you next,

36:36.659 --> 36:38.958
always know that you have
a home here at Anchor Beach.

36:40.128 --> 36:42.920
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

36:42.930 --> 36:44.622
Talya Banks, UC Berkeley!

36:44.632 --> 36:47.091
(CHEERING)

36:47.101 --> 36:49.268
Wyatt Casey, Claremont McKenna College!

36:50.672 --> 36:52.104
Woo-hoo, Wyatt!

36:53.474 --> 36:56.066
Brandon Foster, Musician's Institute!

36:56.076 --> 36:58.309
(LOUD CHEERING)

37:01.614 --> 37:02.939
Way to go, B!

37:02.949 --> 37:05.508
<i>♪ You and me together ♪</i>

37:05.518 --> 37:07.610
<i>♪ We can change the world ♪</i>

37:07.620 --> 37:12.049
<i>♪ You and me together you
and me, and me together ♪</i>

37:12.059 --> 37:15.885
Callie Adams Foster, UCSD
Five Year Law Program!

37:15.895 --> 37:18.762
(CHEERING, WHISTLING)

37:19.765 --> 37:21.057
<i>♪ You and me can ♪</i>

37:21.067 --> 37:22.725
<i>♪ Oh, all I have ♪</i>

37:22.735 --> 37:25.027
<i>♪ You and I ♪</i>

37:25.037 --> 37:27.863
I got a call from
UCSD about an hour ago.

37:27.873 --> 37:30.131
I guess that professor
really did go to bat for you.

37:30.141 --> 37:32.133
(LAUGHING)

37:32.143 --> 37:33.935
Congratulations, honey.

37:33.945 --> 37:36.004
- Thank you.
- I love you.

37:36.014 --> 37:38.173
<i>♪ You and me together ♪</i>

37:38.183 --> 37:40.075
(CHEERING CONTINUES)

37:40.085 --> 37:42.677
<i>♪ Show 'em what it
means to be electric ♪</i>

37:42.687 --> 37:44.278
<i>♪ And good lovers ♪</i>

